Date: Mon, 30 Jun 2025 20:01:23 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 3/5] UPSTREAM: DP: wifi: ath12k: Refactor ring allocation,
 setup API's

Ath12k currently support's two different models quad ring model(mon1)
and dual ring model(mon2) which use different hardware rings.

The mon1 arch specific code(rings allocation, initialization and setup)
are moved to new file dp_mon1.c in ath12k/wifi7 directory.

The mon2 arch specific code(rings allocation, initialization and setup)
are part of new file dp_mon2.c in ath12k/wifi7 directory.
To avoid the code duplication between wifi7 and wifi8(upcoming chipsets)
ath12k/wifi7/dp_mon2.c contains mon2 monitor ops table.
and the definition of these functions are written in dp_mon.c in
ath12k. As the rings are common between wifi7 and upcoming wifi8 chipsets.

Patch-dependency:
	0402-0002-UPSTREAM-DP-wifi-ath12k-Add-architecture-specific-op.patch

Signed-off-by: Sushant Butta <sbutta@qti.qualcomm.com>
